Business Brief -- Calnetics Corp.:
   Company Held by Chairman
   Increases Its Stake to 39%
The men didn't give a reason for the transaction, except
to say that they reached agreement on the price, which they
didn't disclose. Mr. Sacks had been Calnetics's second
largest shareholder.
   Steven Strawn, president of Manchester Plastics, was named
a director, succeeding Mr. Sacks. Calnetics is a Chatsworth,
Calif., maker of molded plastic parts for the building
materials and industrial plastics industries.